## 3. Interactive Elements

- **Navigation:** Features a sticky navigation bar and a visually striking full-screen menu overlay. The menu overlay uses large, italicized serif text that elevates the navigational experience to feel premium.
- **Hover States:** Interactive elements (buttons, nav links, and cards) feature smooth transitions (`duration-500`). Buttons use rounded-pill shapes which are friendly and non-aggressive.
- **LMS Portal:** The member portal is well-structured with a functional sidebar for course navigation and a clear progress tracking system highlighting the accent color.

## 4. Visibility & Usability Issues

> [!WARNING]
> Several contrast and visibility issues were identified that could impact accessibility (WCAG compliance) and general usability.

- **Hero Navigation Contrast:** The previously noted contrast issue on the navbar appears to have been resolved successfully!
- **Color Contrast (Accessibility):** Several sections use the salmon-colored text (`#E9967A`) on white or teal backgrounds. This often fails WCAG 2.1 AA contrast requirements for readability, especially for users with visual impairments.
- **Text Hierarchy:** Some subheading text (especially the "Program details" on the Programs page) is quite small and faint, which can hinder readability on smaller mobile displays or for users skimming the content.

## 5. Programs Page "Flagship" Tile Review

> [!WARNING]
> The "Flagship" (Healing Hearts Program) tile on the Programs page has several critical visual issues that contribute to a "muddy" or "busy" appearance.

![Updated Programs Page Review Recording](C:/Users/chase/.gemini/antigravity/brain/111e353d-0e8a-4ca0-8ff9-f2ce09e9c38d/updated_website_programs_review_1771886840064.webp)

- **Color Contrast & Vibration:** 
  - The coral/orange text on the teal background creates a visual vibration effect. 
  - **Critical Issue:** The italicized text at the bottom right ("+ 4 advanced modules...") is nearly illegible due to the dark red/brown color on the teal background.
  - **Badge Contrast:** The "Premium Flagship Offering" badge uses light grey text on teal, resulting in very low contrast.
- **Alignment & Layout:** The horizontal alignment between the left column (Program Title) and the right column ("What's Inside") is inconsistent, creating an unbalanced top edge.
- **Typography:** Mixing a bold sans-serif ("Healing Hearts") with a serif italic ("Program") adds visual complexity when combined with vibrant colors.
- **Call to Action (CTA):** The "Enroll in the Full Program" button looks like plain white text and lacks a strong visual affordance for a flagship program.

---

## 6. Recommendations Action Plan

Based on the evaluation, here is a prioritized list of recommendations to enhance the UI/UX:

1. **Fix Flagship Tile Contrast:** Change the coral headings inside the teal tile to **White** or a very **Pale Peach**. Fix the illegible italicized text by changing it to **White** or **High-opacity Light Grey**.
2. **Elevate the Flagship Badge:** Give the "Premium Flagship Offering" badge a solid background (e.g., pale gold or white) with dark text to feel truly premium.
3. **Enhance Flagship CTA:** Transform the "Enroll" button into a solid visual element (e.g., a white pill-shaped button) so it stands out as the primary action.
4. **Harmonize Alignment in Flagship Tile:** Vertically align the "Healing Hearts" title with the "What's Inside" heading. Increase the internal padding of the "What's Inside" box.
5. **Adjust Overall Accent Color Contrast:** Darken the Salmon/Coral accent slightly when used for text across the site to ensure it meets a minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio against light backgrounds.
6. **Standardize Body Text & Subheadings:** Increase the weight or size of secondary sub-headings to improve the information hierarchy.
7. **Implement Active States for Links:** Add distinct "active" states (e.g., underlines or color shifts) for navigation links.
